<p>28.  Paraguay &#8226; No information on any instances of secret detention. All 
arrests should be carried out within the legal framework.  
</p>
<p>&#8226; Paraguay does not have any specific anti-terrorism laws, so 
that all crimes are dealt with in accordance with the Penal 
code. There is a draft law currently being considered in 
relation to anti-terrorism measures.  
</p>
<p>&#8226; No information of any secret detention facilities, nor are there 
any plans for construction of such sites.  
</p>
<p>&#8226; No involvement or collaboration in secret detention on the 
territory of another State. 
